threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a malicious loader. It loads a DLL named 'msfltr32.dll', which is not a standard Windows library. It then resolves an obfuscated function from this DLL and executes it in an infinite loop, with a long, randomized sleep of 90-180 minutes between executions. This behavior is characteristic of a backdoor beaconing to a command-and-control (C2) server. The primary IOC is the loading of the payload 'msfltr32.dll'.
